modules.description: Provides functions to establish and manage UDP-based connections, including sending and receiving data, setting timeouts, and handling connection events. Works with socket descriptors, byte sequences, and custom connection state structures. Used to implement low-latency, reliable communication in networked applications such as real-time data transfer or peer-to-peer protocols.

Handles UDP socket initialization, connection, and communication using Lwt for asynchronous I/O. Operates on socket and context types to manage data transmission and reception. Enables real-time data exchange between network endpoints with non-blocking read and write operations.

Provides functions to initialize and manage a UDP-based communication context, including creating sockets, establishing connections, sending data, and handling timeouts. Operates with custom types such as context, socket, and a Bigarray-based buffer for efficient data manipulation. Used to implement real-time data transmission and network event processing in low-latency applications.
